By Peter Uwumarogie  Gombe – Gov. Inuwa Yahaya of Gombe State has felicitated with Vice President Yemi Osinbajo on the occasion of his 63rd birthday. A statement by the governor’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Mr Ismail Misilli on Sunday in Gombe, said that Yahaya described Osinbajo as a cerebral leader, with exceptional humility. According to him, these qualities of the vice president have always manifested while carrying out his duties. Yahaya noted that Osinbajo who is also the Chairman of the Nigerian Economic Council (NEC) had always brought to bear, his acumen, and demonstrated experience and patriotism in handling matters of national interest. He commended Osinbajo’s exemplary leadership, loyalty and commitment to nation building. While wishing the Vice President a happy birthday celebration, he prayed God Almighty to continue to bless Osinbajo with good health and many more years of robust service to Nigeria. (NAN)